# Next.js Frontend

Port of the Vite prototype (`../barber-house-charm`). Keep design + domain logic; swap router + data layer.

## Structure

- Route groups: `(marketing)`, `(public)` (book + shop), `(auth)`, `(portal)`, `(dashboard)`. `onboarding` + `select-plan` are post-login, no shell.
- Server Components for read-mostly aggregation pages (parallel server fetch).
- Client Components only for: calendars, drag-drop, POS keypad, QR scanner, chat, maps, command palette, framer-motion.

## Data

- All data via the typed client in `lib/api-client.ts` (generated from `packages/contracts`). No direct DB, no `db.from(...)`.
- TanStack Query with keys `['org', orgId, entity, params]`. Org id from `GET /me` (short stale time).
- Realtime: subscribe to the WS hub, then `setQueryData` patch or targeted `invalidateQueries`.
- No Server Action that re-implements a business rule; at most a thin BFF proxy to Go with Zod.

## Domain logic comes from contracts

- Nav, mode terms, feature→plan map, pricing read from `packages/contracts/domain/*.json`. Do NOT hardcode `BARBER_NAV`-style arrays in components.
- Sidebar renders from a manifest filtered by `{mode, role, features}`. Multi-mode = merged union, deduped by `section:path` (not "fall back to barber").
- Feature gating in UI is cosmetic; never assume it protects data.

## Components

- Thin pages: page = fetch + layout; logic in `components/<feature>/` + hooks.
- Use the shared `<DataTable>` (columns/data/pagination/sort/filter) — don't re-roll `ui/table.tsx` per page.
- Use shadcn primitives from `components/ui`. Provide loading/error/**empty** states (no silent demo fallback).
